title: FAQ – UseMe Labs
description: Answers to common questions about UseMe Labs data handling, pricing, limits and integrations.

hero.headline: Frequently asked questions
hero.subheadline: Quick answers to help you evaluate UseMe Labs.

sections.heading: Where is our data stored?
sections.body: By default data resides in the EU (Frankfurt or Warsaw). We can deploy into your VPC or run a hybrid model where sensitive sources never leave your network.
bullets: Files encrypted with AES-256 at rest and TLS 1.3 in transit
Access logs streamable to your SIEM

sections.heading: Do you train models on our data?
sections.body: No. Your data is used for inference only. Models run on secured servers and cannot persist temporary data outside the execution environment.

sections.heading: What limits apply?
sections.body: Starter includes 500 documents and 10 workflow runs per month. Growth and Enterprise plans offer configurable limits with automatic scaling.

sections.heading: How long do integrations take?
sections.body: Standard integrations with Microsoft 365 or Google Workspace ship within 3–5 business days. Custom API work depends on your infrastructure complexity.

sections.heading: What support is included?
sections.body: Starter offers business-hours email support. Growth adds shared Slack access and recurring success reviews, while Enterprise includes 24/7 coverage and a dedicated CSM.

sections.heading: How do we cancel?
sections.body: Cancel from the admin console at any time. We issue a final invoice and provide a 30-day data export window.
